The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for knowledge tracing in intelligent tutoring systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of side information, which can be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CE) techniques. Finally, the experimental results are based on real education data, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the computer science education (cs.EDU) sub-category.
